course_title: Topics in Mathematics: Prog. for Math.of Data Science

class_notes:
This topics course introduces programming in Python, with an emphasis on the mathematical theory behind popular machine learning algorithms and the efficient computational methods and tools to implement these algorithms.
Prerequisites: MATH 221, MATH 210/211 (can be taken concurrently), MA315 (recommended) and CS 170
Students with the appropriate perquisites will need a permission code to register. Please contact Taylr Tuggle (tatuggl@emory.edu) for permission.
